divs: sighting detailswas in parking lot of dollar general at around 8pm 10\6\12. was putting cart back at storefront when i noticed a fireball hovering above the tree line around the 141 ramp. at first it reminded me of the size of flame on a hot air balloon ride, but it was dark outand there was no objects obscuring the view of this perfectly cylindrical orb that flickered like flame. i hurried up and got my cell phone to record object, and got a video where i zoomed in and followed object until it disappeared out of my line of sight over the building. i got into my car, and proceeded to turn onto kirkwood highway eastbound when i saw 2 more object equidistant and flying the same trajectory as the first. they were the same description as the first. i pulled over to attempt to record them also but they were out of my sight when i had my phone ready. they caught my attention because all tree were so low flying on the horizon.
Summary: total of 3 glowing orb objects sighted only 1 recorded
